history.intro:
Alternatives Ménages, Nature et Marchés (AMEN) was created in the context of the peace process, political transition, and post-conflict democratization in Africa between 1996 and 1998. This period was marked by a sharp deterioration in women's living conditions, characterized notably by:
• The dominance of patriarchal social norms reinforced by the collapse of state authority;
• The overload of women's household and social responsibilities;
• Family separations due to forced displacement, sexual violence, and male mortality.
AMEN was born from the active mobilization of surviving women.
